author: psiwebtn
title: Bombers earn soccer win over No. Lehigh
text:
Bombers earn soccer win over No. Lehigh Tuesday, October 20, 2015 
The Palmerton boys soccer team earned a Colonial League victory against Northern Lehigh Monday. 
BOYS SOCCER 
No. Lehigh-Palmerton 
Palmerton scored five second-half goals to top Northern Lehigh in a Colonial League contest, 6-1. 
Devon Santos and Logan Blasiak each scored twice for the Blue Bombers. Rio Kapur added a goal and an assist during the win. 
Dan Belfonti scored the lone Northern Lehigh goal. 
Palmerton accumulated 16 shots during the win. 
Catasauqua-Tamaqua 
Tamaqua dropped a 3-2 non-league contest to Catasauqua. 
Tyler Hollenbach scored both goals for the Blue Raiders, with Tyler Hinkel assisting on one of the tallies. 
Tamaqua finished the season with a 1-17 record. 
JUNIOR HIGH
